  "text": "Quantitative transport assay of tsO45-G-YFP was essentially done as described before [CITATION_1] . Briefly, depleted cells were infected with Adenovirus engineered to express tsO45-G-YFP for 1 hour at 37uC, and then washed and transferred to 39.5uC for 16 hours. Transport assays were carried out by shifting cells to 32uC for the times indicated. The cells were then paraformaldehyde-fixed and proceeded for immunofluorescence as described above.",
